# Proposal: Admin Dashboard Final Polish

## Intent
Complete the project by closing the remaining admin finish work: usable workflow UI, backend-authoritative auth UX/state, and catalog-job operational closure. This removes “shell-only admin” and eliminates false access states caused by client-only role flags.

## Scope

### In Scope
- Build must-have admin workflows in UI for products, categories, orders, and catalog jobs using existing admin APIs.
- Replace `sessionStorage`-truth access gating with backend-authoritative auth state (bootstrap from authenticated backend response), including explicit admin login/logout UX and clear 401/403 handling.
- Close catalog job operator dead-ends: implement cancel end-to-end **or** remove/disable cancel affordance until supported; surface row/report errors and actionable status in UI.
- Align frontend admin service typings with backend payload contracts for touched workflows.

### Out of Scope (Non-Goals)
- New business domains (customers, promotions, analytics, etc.).
- Replatforming auth scheme (no JWT/SSO migration in this change).
- Full RBAC redesign beyond current admin role semantics.
- Broad backend API expansion unrelated to admin finish criteria.

## Capabilities

### New Capabilities
- None.

### Modified Capabilities
- `admin-dashboard`: from shell-only route/layout to complete operational workflows for products/categories/orders/catalog jobs.
- `admin-auth-access`: from client-flag gating to backend-authoritative session/access UX state.
- `catalog-job-operations`: from partial operator flow (cancel dead-end/limited diagnostics) to closed-loop operational handling.

## Approach
Use a frontend-first completion pass against existing endpoints, with minimal backend adjustments only where required to remove operational dead-ends and make auth/session truth backend-authoritative. Prefer disabling unsupported actions over shipping broken affordances.

## Affected Areas

| Area | Impact | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| `frontend/src/app/routes/AppRoutes.tsx` | Modified | Add concrete admin workflow routing and guards. |
| `frontend/src/features/admin/layout/AdminShell.tsx` | Modified | Replace placeholder shell with operational navigation/content. |
| `frontend/src/features/admin/auth/adminAccess.ts` | Modified | Backend-authoritative auth/session logic + login/logout state. |
| `frontend/src/features/admin/services/adminOperationsService.ts` | Modified | Contract typing alignment for admin payloads. |
| `backend/src/main/java/com/eltano/ecommerce/catalog/jobs/api/AdminCatalogJobController.java` | Modified (if needed) | Cancel endpoint closure or explicit unsupported behavior contract. |

## Risks

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|------------|------------|
| Auth state regressions causing lockout/false access | Med | Add deterministic 401/403 flows and session bootstrap checks. |
| Job operation inconsistency across UI/API | Med | Single contract decision: implement cancel or hide/disable action. |
| Payload drift causing runtime UI errors | Med | Tighten DTO typing and validate against real responses. |

## Rollback Plan
Revert admin workflow route/component wiring and restore prior guard behavior; if backend cancel changes were introduced, revert controller changes and keep UI cancel disabled. Ship rollback as a single patch release.

## Dependencies
- Existing admin API endpoints and current ROLE_ADMIN security configuration.

## Success Criteria (Metrics)
- [ ] Admin can complete products/categories/orders/catalog job primary flows from UI with no placeholder screens.
- [ ] Access state is backend-authoritative: direct URL/admin refresh behaves consistently with authenticated backend role truth.
- [ ] Catalog jobs have no broken operator actions (cancel works end-to-end or is not presented as actionable).
- [ ] Job status and error diagnostics are visible and actionable for operators.
- [ ] No P1/P2 defects in admin smoke tests for auth, workflow navigation, and job operations.
